docs.abstract: Jess Ravich, one of the highest-ranking executives to be accused of sexual misconduct in the #MeToo era, left TCW, the giant bond-investment firm.
docs.snippet: Jess Ravich, one of the highest-ranking executives to be accused of sexual misconduct in the #MeToo era, left TCW, the giant bond-investment firm.
docs.lead_paragraph: Jess Ravich, one of the most senior Wall Street executives to have been publicly accused of sexual harassment, has departed TCW, the giant bond-fund manager where he was one of the top officials, according to a TCW spokesman.

headline.main: Top Wall Street Executive, Accused of Sexual Harassment, Departs TCW
headline.print_headline: Noted Investor, Facing Lawsuit For Misconduct, Departs Firm

docs.abstract: Christine Lagarde will become one of the most powerful figures in international finance, giving her a leading hand in the world’s second largest economy.
docs.snippet: Christine Lagarde will become one of the most powerful figures in international finance, giving her a leading hand in the world’s second largest economy.
docs.lead_paragraph: During a recent appearance on “The Daily Show,” the host Trevor Noah asked Christine Lagarde if she was familiar with the “glass cliff.” It is the phenomenon, he said, of handing a job to a woman at a hazardous moment, making her success highly improbable, and giving men some deniability.

headline.main: In Tense Times, ‘Call in the Woman’: Lagarde Will Lead the E.C.B.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Bank of England on Thursday raised its growth forecast for the British economy through the next three years, and said it might need to raise its benchmark interest rate more than once over that period to control inflation.

headline.main: Bank of England Foresees Faster Economic Growth
headline.print_headline: Central Bank of the U.K. Foresees 3 Years of Faster Economic Growth

docs.abstract: Though details are scarce, any peace that leaves higher American tariffs in place could continue to hurt China’s status as the world’s factory floor.
docs.snippet: Though details are scarce, any peace that leaves higher American tariffs in place could continue to hurt China’s status as the world’s factory floor.
docs.lead_paragraph: OSAKA, Japan — The spin from President Trump and China’s propaganda machines on Saturday portrayed a truce in a trade war that has shaken economies and markets around the world. Tariffs won’t rise further, at least not yet. And the United States will loosen its potentially devastating punishments against Huawei, China’s most successful multinational company.

headline.main: A China-U.S. Trade Truce Could Enshrine a Global Economic Shift
headline.print_headline: U.S. Trade Truce Could Unseat China as World’s Factory Floor
